# Internationalization (LiftShift)

## Stack

- [`i18next`](https://www.i18next.com/) + `react-i18next`; init in [`frontend/i18n/i18n.ts`](frontend/i18n/i18n.ts).
- Locale files: [`frontend/locales/en.ts`](frontend/locales/en.ts) (default) and [`frontend/locales/ru.ts`](frontend/locales/ru.ts).

## Rules for new copy

1. **Add keys to both `en` and `ru`** in the same commit/change. Do not ship Russian-only or English-only keys except during a short WIP (finish before merge).
2. Use **nested keys** with dot notation, e.g. `log.saveWorkout`, `preferences.title`. Keep groups stable (`nav`, `log`, `preferences`, …).
3. In components: `const { t } = useTranslation();` then `t('log.saveWorkout')`. For interpolation use `t('key', { name: value })` and matching `{{name}}` in strings.
4. **No user-visible English literals** in TSX for navigation, settings, workout log, modals, or errors shown to the user—unless the string is a proper noun (e.g. app name, third-party brand).

## Language switch

- User choice persists via i18next (`liftshift_locale`). Do not invent a second locale storage key for the same purpose.
